writers there
is no concordance,
and agreement, in certaintie
of any nominated particular;
but as the tree is knowne by his
fruites, so it is euident by this Psalm,
and the manifold comfortable matter

therein contained, that he was a
singular sanctified &amp; holy Prophet
of God, who wrote the same, by the
speciall inspiration of Gods holy
Spirit. And it appeareth more particularly
that the certaine Author
thereof was Dauid, being then a
young man in Sauls Court, then
greatly corrupted (as by his collation
verse, 100. appeareth) and that
hee did meditate this Psalme not1. Sa. 17. 49.
