couragious Ioshua, who went
thorow a narrow passage ouer
Iorden, vnto the land of Canaan,
with Gods Arke before him, &amp; by
many battels ouercame and obtayned
the same; as thou must by many
battels, betwixt the flesh &amp; the
spirit, obtaine that eternal Canaan,
walking towards it in a narrowe
passage, and hauing Gods worde
continually before the eyes of thy
heart, to redresse and conforme thy

