of Gods word, let euery yong man
take heed vnto the way of his manners,
to redresse the same in a godly
and comely forme, reuerencing &amp;
honouring, first, his superiours any
way, and elders: secondly, his equalls:
and thirdly, his inferiours.
Concerning the honouring of our

superiours &amp; elders, according to
Gods word; the first precept of our
dutie towards our neighbour, in
Gods Law, commandeth all yong
