mistrust and suspicion, from suspicion
dislike, from dislike hatred,
from hatred, vnchristian breaking
forth in open dissention vpon the
least occasion offred, and so the
bond of peace and christian loue,
which is the life of Religion, is altogether
broken, and cast off, liuing
so, not as Christians, but as
rude, sauage, and cruel wild beasts,
maligning, detracting, despising,
and seeking the mutual destruction
